            "NewJeans 2nd EP \'Get Up\' - 2023",
            "NewJeans (MINJI, HANNI, DANIELLE, HAERIN, and HYEIN) made their debut on July 22, 2022 as the first group to debut from ADOR, an independent label under HYBE led by Hee Jin Min. The quintet aspires to push the limits of K-pop with honest and authentic music that exudes youth. Just like a pair of jeans that has been a staple of every wardrobe for generations, NewJeans aim to allure the listeners with timeless music to be kept in your daily music playlist. The act released New Jeans on August 1, 2022, instantly captivating the global audience and becoming the first K-pop band to achieve the million-seller milestone with their debut album. One of the title tracks “Hype Boy” charted on Billboard Global 200 for 37 consecutive weeks - the longest record from any K-pop female act. NewJeans continue to amaze the world with groundbreaking records while staying true to their musical flair and intrinsic charm, charting on Billboard Hot 100 within less than half a year of their debut with global smash hits “Ditto” and “OMG,” peaking at 74 and 82, respectively. NewJeans also broke the Guinness World Record as the fastest K-pop act to reach one billion streams on Spotify, further demonstrating their widespread global presence. Continuing their upward trajectory, NewJeans will make history as the first K-pop female band to perform at Lollapalooza in Chicago and Summer Sonic in Japan.",
